## Rider Dashboard frontend (Vite)
## Set this to your backend base URL for API calls.
## If unset: dev uses http://localhost:3000/admin/api; production uses same-origin /api
## (dashboard server.js proxies /api -> BACKEND_URL/admin/api). For static hosting without that proxy,
## set VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-host/admin/api
##
## Examples:
## - Local backend:       http://localhost:3000/admin/api
## - Phone on same Wi‑Fi: http://192.168.1.50:3000/admin/api
## - Production:          https://your-domain.com/admin/api
## Optional: abort API requests after this many ms (prevents the UI from waiting forever if the server stops responding).
# VITE_API_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS=75000
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/admin/api

